theorem Topology.closure_interior_union_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (interior (A ∪ B)) = closure (interior A) ∪ closure (interior B) := by
  -- First, rewrite the interior of the union as the union of interiors.
  have h₁ : interior (A ∪ B) = interior A ∪ interior B := by
    simpa using interior_union (A := A) (B := B)
  -- Then use the fact that `closure` distributes over finite unions.
  simpa [h₁] using closure_union (interior A) (interior B)

theorem interior_union
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A B : Set X) :
    interior (A ∪ B : Set X) = interior (A ∪ B) :=
  rfl
